Package: ytblock
Version: 1.0-1
Architecture: linux-any
Maintainer: ytblock maintainer <root@localhost>
Depends: gnupg, e2fsprogs, xxd
Recommends: perl
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Description: Self-discipline internet blocker kernel module
 ytblock is a Linux kernel module that blocks network access
 to user-configured domains and IPs for a time-limited period.
 .
 Designed as a focus tool: once enabled, it is deliberately
 difficult to disable early. Supports PGP-based key escrow
 so a trusted remote party can authorize unblocking.
 .
 Blocking is disabled by default after installation.
 Use 'ytblockctl enable <minutes>' to activate.
